        "timestamp": "2017-07-17 13:30:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nwe would need the policy/engine project updated also before doing a merge with all 3 (common, drools-pdp, engine).",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "694e9904516477db945596a07c0a5d567724e044",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-18 19:59:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nthanks for the changes, these are painful I know, so thank you!   Yeah, as Pam said, commons repo, is used by drools-pdp, and policy/engine, so these changes by themselves will break the others if submitted in isolation.\n\nI suggest to follow this sequence to do the renaming:\n\n1. change the drools-pdp + docker code with the exception of those references in common.    I think these are only contained in features-eelf.\n\n2. change the drools-applications + engine (I think no docker changes are needed, nor common repo dependencies).\n\n3. change the policy-engine + docker with the exception of those references in common.\n\n4. change commons, and missing pieces from 1), 2), 3), and 4).\n\nObviously, there has to be some degree of testing being invasive ..\n\nWe can probably step the changes over several blackout days (with no submissions) ..\n\nI'll follow conversation by email since it will involved other people helping at least with testing.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
